ZH: 我的狗今天需要打针。
EN: My dog needs to get a shot today.

ZH: 我很害怕打针。
EN: I am very afraid of getting shots.

ZH: 小孩子打针时会哭。
EN: Children often cry when they get shots.

ZH: 去年我打了流感疫苗。
EN: I got a flu shot last year.

ZH: 打针可以保护我们免受疾病侵害。
EN: Getting shots can protect us from diseases.

ZH: 我的妹妹今天去打针了。
EN: My sister went to get a shot today.

ZH: 打针可能会有些疼痛。
EN: Getting a shot may be a bit painful.

ZH: 我每年都会去医院打针。
EN: I go to the hospital to get shots every year.

ZH: 医生建议我接种水痘疫苗。
EN: The doctor recommended that I get a chickenpox vaccine.

ZH: 我的臂部很疼，因为我刚打了针。
EN: My arm hurts because I just got a shot.

ZH: 我不太喜欢打针的感觉。
EN: I don't really like the feeling of getting shots.

ZH: 请坐下来，我要给你打针。
EN: Please sit down, I am going to give you a shot.

ZH: 很多人害怕打针。
EN: Many people are afraid of getting shots.

ZH: 打针是保持健康的一种方式。
EN: Getting shots is a way to stay healthy.

ZH: 我的小猫需要去医院打针。
EN: My kitten needs to go to the hospital to get a shot.

ZH: 我今天去打流感疫苗了。
EN: I went to get a flu shot today.

ZH: 不要害怕，打针只是一瞬间的事情。
EN: Don't be afraid, getting a shot is just a momentary thing.

ZH: 你打了针后需要多休息。
EN: You need to rest more after getting a shot.

ZH: 打针需要注意卫生。
EN: It is important to pay attention to hygiene when getting shots.

ZH: 打针的时候要放松。
EN: Relax when getting a shot.
